timetraveller (1.0.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix system-plan --install-schedule under the .deb install.
    The pkexec helper only accepted /usr/local/bin/timetraveller-backup
    (the install.sh path); it now also accepts /usr/bin/timetraveller-backup
    (the .deb path). The worker auto-detects which canonical path exists,
    and the GUI no longer passes a bogus --binary-path computed from the
    site-packages layout for system-plan installs.

 -- Kim McCann <amplogik@gmail.com>  Thu, 21 May 2026 09:00:00 -0700

timetraveller (1.0.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial 1.0 release.
    - Seekable pax+zstd archives with per-file random-access extraction
    - Plan types: Active (scheduled, with retention) and Archive (manual, keep_all)
    - GUI: Plan / Schedule / Archives tabs with switch and remove operations
    - CLI worker with full coverage: --kind, --prune, --extract, --verify,
      --reindex, --list-archives, --list-files, --show-mounts, --show-schedule,
      --install-schedule, --suspend-schedule, --resume-schedule, --remove-plan,
      --switch-to-archive, --switch-to-active
    - Polkit-mediated installation of the system plan's cron entries
    - Built-in Help / About dialog with task-oriented how-tos and search

 -- Kim McCann <amplogik@gmail.com>  Wed, 20 May 2026 20:40:00 -0700
